Build a production-level Python project called "ContentAnalyzer" — an AI agent 
that takes a short-form video video (Instagram/YouTube Shorts/TikTok) and 
identifies what movie scene or real-world event it is from, then explains 
it to the user.

=== TECH STACK ===

- Python 3.11+
- LangChain (agent orchestration)
- yt-dlp (video downloading from links)
- OpenCV (keyframe extraction every 2 seconds)
- ffmpeg + openai-whisper (audio extraction + transcription, use "small" model)
- pytesseract (OCR on keyframes)
- Ollama + Llama 3.1 8B (local reasoning agent, orchestration LLM)
- GPT-4o API + Gemini 1.5 Flash API (vision LLMs, use both, route based on content)
- LangChain DuckDuckGo Search Tool (free, no API key needed)
- FastAPI (REST API backend)
- Pydantic (structured output schemas)
- python-dotenv (env management)
- asyncio (parallel processing of audio + frames + OCR)

